@BeginModule
@Name      = EcaSu
@Title     = Summer days index per time period
@Section   = Climate indices
@Class     = Climate index
@Arguments = ifile ofile
@Operators = eca_su

@BeginDescription
Let @file{ifile} be a time series of the daily maximum temperature TX, then the number of days where 
TX > @math{T} is counted. The number @math{T} is an optional parameter with default @math{T} = 25@celsius. 
Note that TX have to be given in units of Kelvin, whereas @math{T} have to be given in degrees Celsius.
The date information of a timestep in @file{ofile} is the date of the last contributing timestep in @file{ifile}.
@EndDescription
@EndModule


@BeginOperator_eca_su
@Title     = Summer days index per time period
@Parameter = [T]
@EndOperator


@BeginParameter
@Item = T
FLOAT   Temperature threshold (unit: @celsius, default: T = 25@celsius)
@EndParameter


@BeginExample
To get the number of summer days of a time series of daily maximum temperatures use:
@BeginVerbatim
   cdo eca_su txfile ofile
@EndVerbatim
@EndExample
